President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Lanny Erdos of Ohio as the Director of the Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement. Erdos has previously worked at the Ohio Department of Natural Resources and has had extensive experience in the management and regulation of Ohio's coal and aggregate resources. He has also worked with various departments and agencies such as the US and Ohio Environmental Protection Agencies, US Fish and Wildlife, US Army Corps of Engineers, and the Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement.

Additionally, Michael D. Weahkee of New Mexico has been nominated to be the Director of the Indian Health Service at the Department of Health and Human Services. Weahkee, an enrolled member of the Zuni Indian Tribe, has served as the Principal Deputy Director of the Indian Health Service and Assistant Surgeon General of the United States Public Health Services. He has previously served as the chief executive officer at the Phoenix Medical Center and holds degrees in Health Care Management and Health Services Administration and Business Administration.